Cell[TextData[{
 "According to the ",
 ButtonBox["fundamental postulates of quantum mechanics",
  BaseStyle->"Link",
  ButtonData->"paclet:QuantumMob/Q3/tutorial/PostulatesOfQuantumMechanics"],
 ",  the quantum state of a system changes as a consequence of two different \
causes. One is the time-evolution governed by the Schr\[ODoubleDot]dinger \
equation. Both the dynamical and geometric schemes of quantum computation are \
inherently based on such time evolution."
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->1644740873,ExpressionUUID->"a6dbbb9e-6b69-408c-880e-68e07f6b9f11"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The other cause for the change in quantum states is the collapse of the \
quantum states upon measurement, as dictated by ",
 ButtonBox["Postulate 3",
  BaseStyle->"Link",
  ButtonData->"paclet:QuantumMob/Q3/tutorial/MeasurementsOnQuantumStates"],
 ". Can we use this collapse process for quantum computation as well? At \
first glance, it may look absurd when considering the uncontrollable and \
random nature of the collapse of quantum states upon measurement. \
Nevertheless, quantum computation has recently been shown to be possible just \
by employing measurements in different bases, provided the system is prepared \
in a special quantum state called the cluster state or, more generally, the \
graph state (",
 ButtonBox["Raussendorf and Briegel, 2001",
  BaseStyle->"Hyperlink",
  ButtonData->{
    URL["https://doi.org/10.1103/PhysRevLett.86.5188"], None}],
 "; ",
 ButtonBox["Raussendorf et al., 2002",
  BaseStyle->"Hyperlink",
  ButtonData->{
    URL["https://doi.org/10.1080/09500340110107487"], None}],
 "). Such a scheme of quantum computation is the measurement-based quantum \
computation or one-way quantum computation. The reasoning behind the \
\[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]one-way\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] nomenclature will \
become clear below. There are several technical methods to implement \
measurement-based quantum computation. Here, we introduce elementary ideas, \
and we refer interested readers to the aforementioned articles and their \
follow-up literature."
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->568424930,ExpressionUUID->"29869a17-748e-4961-890e-64902cb44d20"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "See also Section 3.4 of the ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  TemplateBox[{
    Cell[
     TextData["Quantum Workbook (2022)"]], 
    "https://doi.org/10.1007/978-3-030-91214-7"},
   "WebLink",
   BaseStyle->{"Text"}]],ExpressionUUID->
  "eef9aa1e-eb73-4fbb-b99f-6361e5f062a9"],
 "."
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->1308734266,ExpressionUUID->"07e41f77-203b-4948-adb1-1c6915b4093c"],

