     PlotRangePadding->Scaled[0.025]],
    Q3`QuantumCircuit[
     Q3`QuantumCircuitIn[
      Q3`ProductState[<|$CellContext`S[1, Q3`$] -> {
          $CellContext`c[0], 
          $CellContext`c[1]}|>, "Label" -> Ket["\[Psi]"]], 
      Ket[<|$CellContext`S[2, Q3`$] -> 0|>]], 
     Q3`Rotation[$CellContext`\[Phi], {0, 0, 1}, 
      $CellContext`S[1, Q3`$]], "Separator", 
     $CellContext`S[2, 6], 
     Q3`CZ[
      $CellContext`S[1, Q3`$], 
      $CellContext`S[2, Q3`$]], {
      $CellContext`S[1, 6], 
      $CellContext`S[2, 6]}]]}]}]], "Picture",
 CellID->1648277011,ExpressionUUID->"062178f1-1122-4830-a3d2-eea08b0a9fd9"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Compared to the previous quantum circuit, this has a single-qubit rotation ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["U", "z"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "2855c313-801d-4cd0-9125-4e9d38473c83"],
 " around the z-axis on the first qubit. In the above expression, the \
equality holds because ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["U", "z"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "3c3dffd0-210a-43ea-a34b-340ff8f08c1c"],
 " commutes with the CZ gate. Applying the previous result to the quantum \
circuit on the right-hand side immediately gives the output state"
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->1576982852,ExpressionUUID->"1a20eef4-58d4-4196-bfda-71fb8b1b27fa"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "\t",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   FractionBox[
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{
      TemplateBox[{"0"},
       "Ket"], "\[CircleTimes]", 
      RowBox[{"(", 
       RowBox[{
        SubscriptBox[
         OverscriptBox["U", "^"], "z"], 
        TemplateBox[{"\[Psi]"},
         "Ket"]}], ")"}]}], "+", 
     RowBox[{
      TemplateBox[{"1"},
       "Ket"], "\[CircleTimes]", 
      RowBox[{"(", 
       RowBox[{
        OverscriptBox["Z", "^"], 
        SubscriptBox[
         OverscriptBox["U", "^"], "z"], 
        TemplateBox[{"\[Psi]"},
         "Ket"]}], ")"}]}]}], 
    SqrtBox["2"]], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "46f58f59-08f4-4d13-aa5b-5143ae6833f4"],
 " ."
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->1769302940,ExpressionUUID->"29e38bbc-3398-41ff-b1a4-03bffb425534"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Upon the measurement of the first qubit, the output state of the second \
qubit becomes either ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox["U", "z"], 
    TemplateBox[{"\[Psi]"},
     "Ket"]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "cd2005e2-e24b-41db-b9f5-631d57a1a6ea"],
 " or  ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"Z", "\[VeryThinSpace]", 
    SubscriptBox["U", "z"], 
    TemplateBox[{"\[Psi]"},
     "Ket"]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "cf7a243b-d144-4f4d-aff3-3c5949ac1a36"],
 " depending on the measurement outcome. In either case, the state  ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox["U", "z"], 
    TemplateBox[{"\[Psi]"},
     "Ket"]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "5c8a23b5-021b-4411-a287-02d59265aa1f"],
 " is achieved on the second qubit by applying an additional operation ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["Z", TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "7d5e3228-ce36-49a9-a2fd-d5ccae68ff5b"],
 " if necessary as follows."
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->1066324268,ExpressionUUID->"f994a3b3-ed80-4438-a26e-c64cdcd6c256"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"\t", 
  InterpretationBox[
   GraphicsBox[{
     {Dashing[{Small, Small}], LineBox[{{{6, -1}, {8, -1}}}]}, 
     LineBox[{{{0, -1}, {6, -1}}, {{0, -2}, {8, -2}}}], {InsetBox[
       StyleBox[
        FormBox[
