  AxesStyle->Large,
  FrameStyle->Large,
  ImagePadding->{{23.400000000000002`, 23.400000000000002`}, {5, 5}},
  ImageSize->298.8,
  PlotRangePadding->Scaled[
   0.025]]],ExpressionUUID->"ec64a1fd-14bc-41c6-8dc1-7740c0f053f6"]], \
"Picture",
 CellID->1320720277,ExpressionUUID->"93b8b997-2d28-4918-8f0f-6b614f695a1f"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["Figure 2",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 ". A preliminary quantum circuit to implement a single-qubit rotation by \
relying on measurement. The label ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox["U", "j"], ":=", 
    RowBox[{
     SubscriptBox["U", "z"], "(", 
     SubscriptBox["\[Phi]", "j"], ")"}]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "4b05af24-1549-4623-b811-22debcf78a4e"],
 " denotes the single-qubit rotation around the z-axis by angle ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Phi]", "j"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "5a364780-4414-4403-afd2-77fdb081bf14"],
 "."
}], "TechNoteCaption",
 CellID->1198628322,ExpressionUUID->"4d8791e1-ff3d-468d-b0eb-5a3b5f7acfb5"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Let us now inspect the implementation of arbitrary single-qubit rotations \
solely based on measurement. Consider the quantum circuit in ",
 ButtonBox["Figure 2",
  BaseStyle->"Link",
  ButtonData->
   "paclet:QuantumMob/Q3/tutorial/MeasurementBasedScheme#1198628322"],
 ". The output state from the quantum circuit can be analyzed by \
consecutively applying the result in ",
 ButtonBox["Figure 1",
  BaseStyle->"Link",
  ButtonData->
   "paclet:QuantumMob/Q3/tutorial/MeasurementBasedScheme#992454319"],
 ". It reads as"
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->619964250,ExpressionUUID->"4d6ea404-8d77-41cf-b649-b8696ff0ff69"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "\t",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    UnderscriptBox["\[CapitalSigma]", 
     RowBox[{
      SubscriptBox["x", "1"], ",", 
      SubscriptBox["x", "2"], ",", 
      SubscriptBox["x", "3"]}]], 
    RowBox[{
     TemplateBox[{
       SubscriptBox["x", "1"]},
      "Ket"], "\[CircleTimes]", 
     TemplateBox[{
       SubscriptBox["x", "2"]},
      "Ket"], "\[CircleTimes]", 
     TemplateBox[{
       SubscriptBox["x", "3"]},
      "Ket"], "\[CircleTimes]", 
     RowBox[{"(", 
      RowBox[{
       SuperscriptBox["Z", 
        SubscriptBox["x", "3"]], 
       RowBox[{
        SubscriptBox["U", "z"], "(", 
        SubscriptBox["\[Phi]", "3"], ")"}], "H", "\[ThinSpace]", 
       SuperscriptBox["Z", 
        SubscriptBox["x", "2"]], 
       RowBox[{
        SubscriptBox["U", "z"], "(", 
        SubscriptBox["\[Phi]", "2"], ")"}], "H", "\[ThinSpace]", 
       SuperscriptBox["Z", 
        SubscriptBox["x", "1"]], 
       RowBox[{
        SubscriptBox["U", "z"], "(", 
        SubscriptBox["\[Phi]", "1"], ")"}], 
       TemplateBox[{"\[Psi]"},
        "Ket"]}], ")"}]}]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "cc5c0a95-4834-4133-972c-ec5844d84bae"],
 " ."
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->671054969,ExpressionUUID->"0308b2b6-a96e-4f18-a52e-aadf91eac4c9"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Using the identity ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"H", "\[ThinSpace]", "Z", " ", "H"}], "=", "X"}], 
   TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->"70dc2252-b808-4ec3-a295-5b5ba768f0eb"],
 ", the final state on the fourth qubit can be written as "
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->1026580557,ExpressionUUID->"27d7d3da-121b-4d8d-a178-e3cfaa0bed21"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "\t",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox[
     TemplateBox[{"\[CapitalPsi]"},
      "Ket"], "4"], "=", 
    RowBox[{
     SuperscriptBox["Z", 
      SubscriptBox["x", "3"]], 
     RowBox[{
      SubscriptBox["U", "z"], "(", 
      SubscriptBox["\[Phi]", "3"], ")"}], 
     SuperscriptBox["X", 
      SubscriptBox["x", "2"]], 
     RowBox[{
      SubscriptBox["U", "x"], "(", 
      SubscriptBox["\[Phi]", "2"], ")"}], 
     SuperscriptBox["Z", 
      SubscriptBox["x", "1"]], 
     RowBox[{
      SubscriptBox["U", "z"], "(", 
      SubscriptBox["\[Phi]", "1"], ")"}], 
     TemplateBox[{"\[Psi]"},
      "Ket"]}]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "99a7d8de-af4e-4652-8181-60f09fa343a1"],
 " ."
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->408081862,ExpressionUUID->"5472901d-7e1d-439e-8b8b-43e970501973"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Furthermore, using the identities ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"X", "\[ThinSpace]", "Z", "\[ThinSpace]", "X"}], "=", 
    RowBox[{"-", "Z"}]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "f68e3d46-cb81-4323-8158-19f108d13c92"],
 " and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"Z", "\[ThinSpace]", "X", "\[ThinSpace]", "Z"}], "=", 
    RowBox[{"-", "X"}]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "483dfd85-5890-4fb5-b85d-e9c8081ce192"],
 ", we arrive at the expression"
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->1037046094,ExpressionUUID->"a03a9842-70a1-4828-8f1d-98bfa92c2546"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "\t",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox[
     TemplateBox[{"\[CapitalPsi]"},
      "Ket"], "4"], "=", 
    RowBox[{
     SuperscriptBox["Z", 
      SubscriptBox["x", "3"]], 
     SuperscriptBox["X", 
      SubscriptBox["x", "2"]], 
     SuperscriptBox["Z", 
      SubscriptBox["x", "1"]], 
     RowBox[{
      SubscriptBox["U", "z"], "(", 
      RowBox[{
       SuperscriptBox[
        RowBox[{"(", 
         RowBox[{"-", "1"}], ")"}], 
        SubscriptBox["x", "2"]], 
       SubscriptBox["\[Phi]", "3"]}], ")"}], 
     RowBox[{
      SubscriptBox["U", "x"], "(", 
      RowBox[{
       SuperscriptBox[
        RowBox[{"(", 
         RowBox[{"-", "1"}], ")"}], 
        SubscriptBox["x", "1"]], 
       SubscriptBox["\[Phi]", "2"]}], ")"}], 
     RowBox[{
      SubscriptBox["U", "z"], "(", 
      SubscriptBox["\[Phi]", "1"], ")"}], 
     TemplateBox[{"\[Psi]"},
      "Ket"]}]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "78d8e689-278b-43f8-b99e-f6b75230de2c"],
 " ."
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->1112696100,ExpressionUUID->"78f89bfe-8f40-477f-a8b6-a21077d518e6"],

Cell["\<\
The key point to notice here is that upon measurement on the first three \
qubits, the fourth qubit take on the state with a single-qubit rotation\
\>", "TechNoteText",
 CellID->915459778,ExpressionUUID->"fa2a3223-18fc-4e3e-960e-fce439373d0f"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "\t",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{
     SubscriptBox["U", "z"], "(", 
     RowBox[{
      SuperscriptBox[
       RowBox[{"(", 
        RowBox[{"-", "1"}], ")"}], 
       SubscriptBox["x", "2"]], 
      SubscriptBox["\[Phi]", "3"]}], ")"}], 
    RowBox[{
     SubscriptBox["U", "x"], "(", 
     RowBox[{
      SuperscriptBox[
       RowBox[{"(", 
        RowBox[{"-", "1"}], ")"}], 
       SubscriptBox["x", "1"]], 
      SubscriptBox["\[Phi]", "2"]}], ")"}], 
    RowBox[{
     SubscriptBox["U", "z"], "(", 
     SubscriptBox["\[Phi]", "1"], ")"}]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "8ae3ee48-6191-4b8d-b3bc-1a51c3a14c8e"],
 " "
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->1440150250,ExpressionUUID->"616edb0c-bdaf-4d63-b9f2-37f1dd00c613"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "operated on the initial state ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   TemplateBox[{"\[Psi]"},
    "Ket"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "87752582-12f1-427b-bd09-185f5fc1232f"],
 " of the first qubit. The rotation consists of three rotations around two \
perpendicular axes, and these are sufficient to realize any arbitrary \
single-qubit rotation (see tutorial \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]",
 ButtonBox["Single-Qubit Gates",
  BaseStyle->"Link",
  ButtonData->"paclet:QuantumMob/Q3/tutorial/SingleQubitGates"],
 "\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote])."
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->196003581,ExpressionUUID->"842949fb-0397-4fb3-9647-f740e80e66ce"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The rotation achieved above through the quantum circuit in ",
 ButtonBox["Figure 2",
  BaseStyle->"Link",
  ButtonData->
   "paclet:QuantumMob/Q3/tutorial/MeasurementBasedScheme#1198628322"],
 " is not deterministic since the direction (clockwise or anti-clockwise) \
depends on outcomes ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["x", "1"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "49938fab-d9a2-426a-ac04-07d427bf1d8a"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["x", "2"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "0f1a7f84-a369-4443-8529-5549aa575c7f"],
 ", and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["x", "3"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "40361c75-8c13-4d45-ac5b-4cbba08bd106"],
 " of the measurement on the first three qubits. However, we can make it \
deterministic by delaying the operations on the second qubit until after \
measurement on the first qubit and then operation on the third qubit until \
after measurement on the second qubit. "
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->1564747894,ExpressionUUID->"81290c59-e396-49c2-95e3-41ee19eb0573"],

