      StripOnInput->False,
      FontSize->Scaled[0.016666666666666666`],
      FontWeight->"Light",
      FontSlant->Italic], {23, -4}, NCache[
     ImageScaled[{Rational[1, 2], Rational[1, 2]}], 
      ImageScaled[{0.5, 0.5}]]]}},
  AxesStyle->Large,
  FrameStyle->Large,
  ImagePadding->{{23.400000000000002`, 23.400000000000002`}, {1, 1}},
  ImageSize->910.8000000000001,
  PlotRange->NCache[{Full, {
      Rational[-9, 2], 
      Rational[-1, 2]}}, {Full, {-4.5, -0.5}}],
  PlotRangePadding->Scaled[
   0.025]]],ExpressionUUID->"4aeacf7b-1bc8-47cb-9f0c-69cfecbf258c"]], \
"Picture",
 CellID->895424692,ExpressionUUID->"fe54da99-caa9-45e5-920e-477e45cfe7f1"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["Figure 3",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 ". Quantum circuit to implement deterministically single-qubit rotation \
based on measurement (and classical feedback control). Notations are the same \
as in ",
 ButtonBox["Figure 2",
  BaseStyle->"Link",
  ButtonData->
   "paclet:QuantumMob/Q3/tutorial/MeasurementBasedScheme#1198628322"],
 ". In many cases, the classical feedback controls (after then second \
vertical dotted line) on the forth qubit are not necessary."
}], "TechNoteCaption",
 CellID->1984883915,ExpressionUUID->"896954e7-686c-4908-b813-b78de0a649f9"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Consider the modified quantum circuit in ",
 ButtonBox["Figure 3",
  BaseStyle->"Link",
  ButtonData->
   "paclet:QuantumMob/Q3/tutorial/MeasurementBasedScheme#1984883915"],
 ". We first set ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox["\[Phi]", "1"], "=", "\[Gamma]"}], TraditionalForm]],
  ExpressionUUID->"4e60bc2b-c1c0-469e-a7c8-69a55815d11d"],
 ". Then, depending on the measurement outcome ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["x", "1"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "2840e0c8-7720-4edc-aad3-5d347ce375ee"],
 " on the first qubit, we set ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox["\[Phi]", "2"], "=", 
    RowBox[{
     SuperscriptBox[
      RowBox[{"(", 
       RowBox[{"-", "1"}], ")"}], 
      SubscriptBox["x", "1"]], "\[Beta]"}]}], TraditionalForm]],
  ExpressionUUID->"397d3273-4234-4270-80dd-d44811403931"],
 ". Similarly, depending on the measurement outcome ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["x", "2"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "1c32d465-1b52-43b4-8307-5e462efc896d"],
 " on the second qubit, we set ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox["\[Phi]", "3"], "=", 
    RowBox[{
     SuperscriptBox[
      RowBox[{"(", 
       RowBox[{"-", "1"}], ")"}], 
      SubscriptBox["x", "2"]], "\[Alpha]"}]}], TraditionalForm]],
  ExpressionUUID->"d5ef0135-b87a-48fe-ba86-d1506f151c63"],
 ". The final state on the fourth qubit will become"
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->72106201,ExpressionUUID->"58be4621-f357-4362-a69c-eb4297c3fc08"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "\t",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox[
     TemplateBox[{"\[CapitalPsi]"},
      "Ket"], "4"], "=", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{
      SuperscriptBox["Z", 
       SubscriptBox["x", "3"]], 
      SuperscriptBox["X", 
       SubscriptBox["x", "2"]], 
      SuperscriptBox["Z", 
       SubscriptBox["x", "1"]], 
      RowBox[{
       SubscriptBox["U", "z"], "(", "\[Alpha]", ")"}], 
      RowBox[{
       SubscriptBox["U", "x"], "(", "\[Beta]", ")"}], 
      RowBox[{
       SubscriptBox["U", "z"], "(", "\[Gamma]", ")"}], 
      TemplateBox[{"\[Psi]"},
       "Ket"]}], "=", 
     RowBox[{
      SuperscriptBox["Z", 
       SubscriptBox["x", "3"]], 
      SuperscriptBox["X", 
       SubscriptBox["x", "2"]], 
      SuperscriptBox["Z", 
       SubscriptBox["x", "1"]], 
      RowBox[{"U", "(", 
       RowBox[{"\[Alpha]", ",", "\[Beta]", ",", "\[Gamma]"}], ")"}], 
      TemplateBox[{"\[Psi]"},
       "Ket"]}]}]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "a5cfae78-6031-4de0-91a5-0e3d35d0313f"]
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->1931988752,ExpressionUUID->"ee601245-7d64-43e2-8c0b-fff745ef5af4"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "with the single-qubit Euler rotation ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"U", "(", 
    RowBox[{"\[Alpha]", ",", "\[Beta]", ",", "\[Gamma]"}], ")"}], 
   TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->"b3df3416-6ce7-4f59-9455-d8b2d05a4206"],
 " fixed ",
 StyleBox["deterministically",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 ". There are still undesired operations, ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    SuperscriptBox["Z", 
     SubscriptBox["x", "3"]], 
    SuperscriptBox["X", 
     SubscriptBox["x", "2"]], 
    SuperscriptBox["Z", 
     SubscriptBox["x", "1"]]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "0bf04ded-3506-456e-a94f-8d555e1335d6"],
 ". However, these operations are irrelevant at the end of quantum \
computation, and do not have to be corrected. For example, if the final state \
is measured in the logical basis, ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["Z", TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "c84b4e18-357e-4af9-b388-0e441dfb4658"],
 " does not affect the readout at all, and the effect of ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["X", TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "27f7c789-731a-46cb-a141-41b805d5c96b"],
 " can be handled by a classical post-processing. If really necessary, one \
can always remove them by further feedback controls as in the last part of \
the quantum circuit in ",
 ButtonBox["Figure 3",
  BaseStyle->"Link",
  ButtonData->
   "paclet:QuantumMob/Q3/tutorial/MeasurementBasedScheme#1984883915"],
 ". "
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->2114992197,ExpressionUUID->"aede4c14-bdc5-4d22-ac4a-3a161248d666"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[TextData[{
 "Demonstration: ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox["R", "Z"], "(", "\[Phi]", ")"}], TraditionalForm]],
  ExpressionUUID->"01ddb46e-1558-4128-b8f1-a4f080d8cc8c"]
}], "Subsection",
 CellID->779760083,ExpressionUUID->"72c503e0-26f6-4eac-830d-8cf7505a1976"],

Cell["\<\
Although it is already clear that the elementary building block directly \
gives the rotation around the z-axis, we start the demonstration with it to \
establish a systematic way to achieve rotations around other axes. In this \
method, rotation around the z-axis is the simplest, the rotation around \
x-axis requires one more layer of measurements and feedback controls, and \
rotations around any other axes can be achieved through three layers of \
measurements and feedback controls.\
\>", "TechNoteText",
 CellID->223562395,ExpressionUUID->"f5fbaae8-425c-4624-80a9-e6847cb00998"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"Needs", "[", "\"\<QuantumMob`Q3`\>\"", "]"}]], "Input",
 CellLabel->"In[9]:=",
 CellID->1165611463,ExpressionUUID->"81b3a3b0-250e-430c-8a24-faf0bc1b4481"],

Cell[BoxData[{
 RowBox[{"Let", "[", 
  RowBox[{"Qubit", ",", "S"}], "]"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
 RowBox[{"Let", "[", 
  RowBox[{"Real", ",", "c", ",", "\[Phi]"}], "]"}]}], "Input",
 CellLabel->"In[10]:=",
 CellID->1766928076,ExpressionUUID->"04e8ee1e-cf1d-4501-84d5-73271923fb05"],

Cell["Prepare the first qubit in an arbitrary initial state:", \
"TechNoteMathCaption",
 CellID->2020817249,ExpressionUUID->"47fdecc3-1908-4820-ae01-b040921f4243"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"in", "=", 
  RowBox[{"ProductState", "[", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"S", "[", "1", "]"}], "\[Rule]", 
     RowBox[{"{", 
      RowBox[{
       RowBox[{"c", "[", "0", "]"}], ",", 
       RowBox[{"c", "[", "1", "]"}]}], "}"}]}], ",", 
    RowBox[{"\"\<Label\>\"", "\[Rule]", 
     RowBox[{"Ket", "[", "\"\<\[Psi]\>\"", "]"}]}]}], "]"}]}]], "Input",
 CellLabel->"In[12]:=",
 CellID->1421626638,ExpressionUUID->"d669b655-001d-4ae4-8da9-97f75be03d51"],

Cell[BoxData[
 InterpretationBox[
  TagBox[
   SubscriptBox[
    RowBox[{"(", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{
       InterpretationBox[
        SubscriptBox["c", 
         TemplateBox[{",", "\",\"", "0"},
          "RowWithSeparators"]],
        $CellContext`c[0]], " ", 
       TemplateBox[{"0"},
        "Ket"]}], "+", 
      RowBox[{
       InterpretationBox[
        SubscriptBox["c", 
         TemplateBox[{",", "\",\"", "1"},
          "RowWithSeparators"]],
        $CellContext`c[1]], " ", 
       TemplateBox[{"1"},
        "Ket"]}]}], ")"}], 
    InterpretationBox[
     SubscriptBox["S", 
      TemplateBox[{",", "\",\"", "1"},
       "RowWithSeparators"]],
     $CellContext`S[1, QuantumMob`Q3`$]]],
   DisplayForm],
  QuantumMob`Q3`ProductState[<|$CellContext`S[1, QuantumMob`Q3`$] -> {
      $CellContext`c[0], 
      $CellContext`c[1]}|>, "Label" -> Ket["\[Psi]"]]]], "Output",
 CellLabel->"Out[12]=",
 CellID->313076105,ExpressionUUID->"88b12c78-1faa-488b-a933-56590888831a"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell["\<\
Build the overall quantum circuit in two steps indicated by the vertical \
dashed line. The first step corresponds to the preparation, and the second to \
the operation:\
\>", "TechNoteMathCaption",
 CellID->1133711781,ExpressionUUID->"347a9277-e1e8-4d4a-b1f9-1bfb2ef933be"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"qc", "=", 
  RowBox[{"QuantumCircuit", "[", 
   RowBox[{"in", ",", 
    RowBox[{"Ket", "[", 
     RowBox[{"S", "@", 
      RowBox[{"{", "2", "}"}]}], "]"}], ",", "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
    RowBox[{"S", "[", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"{", "2", "}"}], ",", "6"}], "]"}], ",", 
    RowBox[{"CZ", "[", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"S", "[", "1", "]"}], ",", 
      RowBox[{"S", "[", "2", "]"}]}], "]"}], ",", "\"\<Separator\>\"", ",", 
    "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
    RowBox[{"Rotation", "[", 
     RowBox[{"\[Phi]", ",", 
      RowBox[{"S", "[", 
       RowBox[{"1", ",", "3"}], "]"}]}], "]"}], ",", 
    RowBox[{"S", "[", 
     RowBox[{"1", ",", "6"}], "]"}], ",", 
    RowBox[{"Measurement", "[", 
     RowBox[{"S", "[", 
      RowBox[{"1", ",", "3"}], "]"}], "]"}]}], "]"}]}]], "Input",
 CellLabel->"In[13]:=",
 CellID->1818987083,ExpressionUUID->"ddf01aad-c870-47d1-9d9e-a6679e5ecaf6"],

