Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["Figure 4",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 ". A primitive quantum circuit to implement the CNOT gate relying on \
measurement."
}], "TechNoteCaption",
 CellID->719836414,ExpressionUUID->"f352b71e-afdc-4da6-a3f5-992ad6a8dbf0"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Let us now construct a quantum circuit to implement a CNOT gate in the \
measurement-based scheme. There are several ways to do so, and here we adopt \
the example described by the quantum circuit in ",
 ButtonBox["Figure 4",
  BaseStyle->"Link",
  ButtonData->
   "paclet:QuantumMob/Q3/tutorial/MeasurementBasedScheme#719836414"],
 ". The first two CNOT gates brings the input state to "
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->1158429812,ExpressionUUID->"b8050ba4-4087-4f43-a507-f2bfb44982ac"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "\t",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    TemplateBox[{
      SubscriptBox["x", "1"]},
     "Ket"], "\[CircleTimes]", 
    TemplateBox[{
      SubscriptBox["x", "2"]},
     "Ket"], "\[CircleTimes]", 
    TemplateBox[{
      RowBox[{
        SubscriptBox["x", "1"], "\[CirclePlus]", 
        SubscriptBox["x", "2"]}]},
     "Ket"], "\[CircleTimes]", 
    TemplateBox[{"0"},
     "Ket"]}], TraditionalForm]],
  InitializationCell->True,ExpressionUUID->
  "0783e1cb-1cfc-4307-ae4e-e4096728535d"]
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->838287872,ExpressionUUID->"af289327-4ab4-4c57-91fb-2efa00c225a1"],

Cell["\<\
at the instant indicated by the first vertical dotted line. At the second \
vertical dotted line, the state becomes\
\>", "TechNoteText",
 CellID->1474128255,ExpressionUUID->"ca0dcf26-ef68-453e-8419-e42b862a12f3"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "\t",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    TemplateBox[{
      SubscriptBox["x", "1"]},
     "Ket"], "\[CircleTimes]", 
    TemplateBox[{
      SubscriptBox["x", "2"]},
     "Ket"], "\[CircleTimes]", 
    RowBox[{"(", 
     RowBox[{"H", 
      TemplateBox[{
        RowBox[{
          SubscriptBox["x", "1"], "\[CirclePlus]", 
          SubscriptBox["x", "2"]}]},
       "Ket"]}], ")"}], "\[CircleTimes]", 
    TemplateBox[{"0"},
     "Ket"]}], TraditionalForm]],
  InitializationCell->True,ExpressionUUID->
  "8687dd4a-acab-47da-a1c4-c60011a45e84"],
 " ."
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->776189313,ExpressionUUID->"2f6e6f50-463f-4c81-8a44-831bb0cfa62d"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Now we use ",
 ButtonBox["Figure 1",
  BaseStyle->"Link",
  ButtonData->
   "paclet:QuantumMob/Q3/tutorial/MeasurementBasedScheme#992454319"],
 ", in effect, to transfer the state stored in the third qubit to the fourth \
qubit. This leads to the state"
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->451869751,ExpressionUUID->"2302dc6d-b095-4aba-a46e-9b5b807d3264"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "\t",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{
     UnderscriptBox["\[CapitalSigma]", 
      SubscriptBox["y", "3"]], 
     RowBox[{
      TemplateBox[{
        SubscriptBox["x", "1"]},
       "Ket"], "\[CircleTimes]", 
      TemplateBox[{
        SubscriptBox["x", "2"]},
       "Ket"], "\[CircleTimes]", 
      TemplateBox[{
        SubscriptBox["y", "3"]},
       "Ket"], "\[CircleTimes]", 
      RowBox[{"(", 
       RowBox[{"H", "\[ThinSpace]", 
        SuperscriptBox["Z", 
         SubscriptBox["y", "3"]], "H", 
        TemplateBox[{
          RowBox[{
            SubscriptBox["x", "1"], "\[CirclePlus]", 
            SubscriptBox["x", "2"]}]},
         "Ket"]}], ")"}]}]}], "=", 
    RowBox[{
     UnderscriptBox["\[CapitalSigma]", 
      SubscriptBox["y", "3"]], 
     RowBox[{
      TemplateBox[{
        SubscriptBox["x", "1"]},
       "Ket"], "\[CircleTimes]", 
      TemplateBox[{
        SubscriptBox["x", "2"]},
       "Ket"], "\[CircleTimes]", 
      TemplateBox[{
        SubscriptBox["y", "3"]},
       "Ket"], "\[CircleTimes]", 
      RowBox[{"(", 
       RowBox[{
        SuperscriptBox["X", 
         SubscriptBox["y", "3"]], 
        TemplateBox[{
          RowBox[{
            SubscriptBox["x", "1"], "\[CirclePlus]", 
            SubscriptBox["x", "2"]}]},
         "Ket"]}], ")"}]}]}]}], TraditionalForm]],
  InitializationCell->True,ExpressionUUID->
  "489e1492-e0e7-4a49-a3d4-78e847028562"],
 " ."
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->1780747998,ExpressionUUID->"cdf65872-5e61-436d-ad46-72576e9e8bad"],

Cell["\<\
Finally, applying the Hadamard gate on the second qubit leads to\
\>", "TechNoteText",
 CellID->1193567475,ExpressionUUID->"400b8226-b943-4194-bba3-ca5c15c59215"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "\t",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    UnderscriptBox["\[CapitalSigma]", 
     RowBox[{
      SubscriptBox["y", "2"], ",", 
      SubscriptBox["y", "3"]}]], 
    RowBox[{
     TemplateBox[{
       SubscriptBox["x", "1"]},
      "Ket"], "\[CircleTimes]", 
     TemplateBox[{
       SubscriptBox["y", "2"]},
      "Ket"], "\[CircleTimes]", 
     TemplateBox[{
       SubscriptBox["y", "3"]},
      "Ket"], "\[CircleTimes]", 
     RowBox[{"(", 
      RowBox[{
       SuperscriptBox["X", 
        SubscriptBox["y", "3"]], 
       TemplateBox[{
         RowBox[{
           SubscriptBox["x", "1"], "\[CirclePlus]", 
           SubscriptBox["x", "2"]}]},
        "Ket"]}], ")"}]}], 
    SuperscriptBox[
     RowBox[{"(", 
      RowBox[{"-", "1"}], ")"}], 
     RowBox[{
      SubscriptBox["y", "2"], 
      SubscriptBox["x", "2"]}]]}], TraditionalForm]],
  InitializationCell->True,ExpressionUUID->
  "537b95e5-8694-49ee-901e-8fd81f3bfdad"],
 " ."
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->1053625363,ExpressionUUID->"6dca7fa0-57ee-47ef-a159-34a8a2170923"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The phase factor \[Minus]1 occurs when ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox["x", "2"], "=", 
    RowBox[{
     SubscriptBox["y", "2"], "=", "1"}]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "bc1dfff8-3aa0-4dbe-af70-d83e2cdd62c2"],
 ". By inspection, one can see that the same factor arises when one applies \
",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["Z", TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "e0fb2ea9-d913-47e0-929b-f366edf12c66"],
 " on both the first and fourth qubits. This leads to the final state out of \
the quantum circuit as follows"
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->409591351,ExpressionUUID->"61daae4f-1fc9-4faa-9c4b-f882aa676878"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "\t",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    TemplateBox[{
      SubscriptBox["\[CapitalPsi]", "out"]},
     "Ket"], "=", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{
      UnderscriptBox["\[CapitalSigma]", 
       RowBox[{
        SubscriptBox["y", "2"], ",", 
        SubscriptBox["y", "3"]}]], "(", 
      RowBox[{
       SuperscriptBox["Z", 
        SubscriptBox["y", "2"]], 
       TemplateBox[{
         SubscriptBox["x", "1"]},
        "Ket"]}], ")"}], "\[CircleTimes]", 
     TemplateBox[{
       SubscriptBox["y", "2"]},
      "Ket"], "\[CircleTimes]", 
     TemplateBox[{
       SubscriptBox["y", "3"]},
      "Ket"], "\[CircleTimes]", 
     RowBox[{"(", 
      RowBox[{
       SuperscriptBox["X", 
        SubscriptBox["y", "3"]], 
       SuperscriptBox["Z", 
        SubscriptBox["y", "2"]], 
       TemplateBox[{
         RowBox[{
           SubscriptBox["x", "1"], "\[CirclePlus]", 
           SubscriptBox["x", "2"]}]},
        "Ket"]}], ")"}]}]}], TraditionalForm]],
  InitializationCell->True,ExpressionUUID->
  "c6198324-6934-404d-98a1-354515d532f4"],
 " ."
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->1490523374,ExpressionUUID->"94187c51-8a82-4903-b7ff-b8b79803f23d"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "When one performs measurement on the second and third qubits, depending on \
the outcomes ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["y", "2"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "084fab7d-1d79-4bc5-92bc-2401f036f2a6"],
 " and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["y", "3"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "6cd2c6c8-5372-4184-b604-4262a250fa6f"],
 ", the final state stored in the first and fourth qubits is given by"
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->1432736228,ExpressionUUID->"57ca8fad-64e2-421d-ad8d-3dda0a52dacf"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "\t",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox[
     TemplateBox[{
       SubscriptBox["\[CapitalPsi]", "out"]},
      "Ket"], "14"], "=", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"(", 
      RowBox[{
       SuperscriptBox["Z", 
        SubscriptBox["y", "2"]], 
       TemplateBox[{
         SubscriptBox["x", "1"]},
        "Ket"]}], ")"}], "\[CircleTimes]", 
     RowBox[{"(", 
      RowBox[{
       SuperscriptBox["X", 
        SubscriptBox["y", "3"]], 
       SuperscriptBox["Z", 
        SubscriptBox["y", "2"]], 
       TemplateBox[{
         RowBox[{
           SubscriptBox["x", "1"], "\[CirclePlus]", 
           SubscriptBox["x", "2"]}]},
        "Ket"]}], ")"}]}]}], TraditionalForm]],
  InitializationCell->True,ExpressionUUID->
  "6442ff23-dc36-4b5c-9e9b-db1b707adfc1"],
 " ."
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->1196217257,ExpressionUUID->"0e3ae44d-f7cb-4f81-9ef1-f027f220582a"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Let us ignore the byproduct operators, ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["X", TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "bd10a61f-90f2-49ac-aed0-fa10845a6fd0"],
 " and/or ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["Z", TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "c377b602-aa6b-45e9-a062-947c2a2428e3"],
 ", for the moment. We then see that in this quantum circuit, the first qubit \
plays the role of control qubit. The input state of the target qubit is put \
in the second qubit, and the output state is supposed to appear in the fourth \
qubit."
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->660333035,ExpressionUUID->"cb91555d-4226-4895-be76-fb8266f738b5"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Using the relation between the ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  TemplateBox[{
    Cell[
     TextData["CZ"]], "paclet:QuantumMob/Q3/ref/CZ", 
    "QuantumMob Package Symbol"},
   "PackageLink",
   BaseStyle->"InlineFormula"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontFamily->"Source Sans Pro",ExpressionUUID->
  "bec3a13c-29b4-48aa-9431-7dd166eb225b"],
 " and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  TemplateBox[{
    Cell[
     TextData["CNOT"]], "paclet:QuantumMob/Q3/ref/CNOT", 
    "QuantumMob Package Symbol"},
   "PackageLink",
   BaseStyle->"InlineFormula"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontFamily->"Source Sans Pro",ExpressionUUID->
  "8761003d-18c4-4abf-b388-8dad606cf484"],
 " gates, we can rewrite the quantum circuit in ",
 ButtonBox["Figure 4",
  BaseStyle->"Link",
  ButtonData->
   "paclet:QuantumMob/Q3/tutorial/MeasurementBasedScheme#719836414"],
 " into the new form in ",
 ButtonBox["Figure 5",
  BaseStyle->"Link",
  ButtonData->
   "paclet:QuantumMob/Q3/tutorial/MeasurementBasedScheme#673278988"],
 ". It is clear that once the entanglement is generated among the four \
qubits, then it is sufficient to perform a measurement on the second and \
third qubits to implement the ",
 ButtonBox["CNOT gate",
  BaseStyle->"Link",
  ButtonData->"paclet:QuantumMob/Q3/ref/CNOT"],
 ". One has to apply ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["Z", TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "d28550da-31cd-4507-95ed-730bd7b7a61c"],
 " on both the first and fourth qubit when ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox["y", "2"], "=", "1"}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "c8b15686-3986-44b8-bdc8-096cea9c2ac0"],
 " and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["X", TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "39ceed32-2616-4161-b85e-bf42b9ea8420"],
 " as well if ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox["y", "3"], "=", "1"}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "24f8b815-bf30-49ff-8d4e-03a46a0c0aba"],
 " as indicated in the final part after the vertical dotted line in ",
 ButtonBox["Figure 5",
  BaseStyle->"Link",
  ButtonData->
   "paclet:QuantumMob/Q3/tutorial/MeasurementBasedScheme#673278988"],
 ". But again, in many cases, the additional step is not necessary or can be \
done with simple classical post-processing."
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->399964254,ExpressionUUID->"b9c3b2b8-2e40-4b7d-944d-bba5a785ae39"],

